{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὕᾰλος</b> <br /> or <b>ὕελος</b> (see. below), ἡ, see [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aelius Dionysius Grammaticus “fragment” 217; but in 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Lapidibus” 49 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], ὁ:—the form <b>ὕαλος</b> is said to be <i>Attic dialect</i>, <b>ὕελος</b> Hellenic, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista 281, [prev. author] “PS” p.118 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus, Moer.p.373 P., Thom.Mag.p.365 R.; in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus codices vary between ὕελος\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] and ὕαλο; ὕελος is read in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Posteriora” 88a14, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus [same place], “Ign.” 73, “PHolm.” 10.7, but ὕαλος in LXX.Job.28.17, 1st c.AD: Anonymus Londinensis 39.18, NT.Rev.21.18 \">NT+4th c.BC+</a>]; compare ὑάλινος:—originally <b>some kind of crystalline stone,</b> such as that used by the Ethiopians to enclose their mummies in, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.24; ὕ. ἀργή “Periplus Maris Rubri [1st c.AD]” 49; ὕ. ὀρωρυγμένη \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>rock-crystal,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Achilles Tatius Astronomus 2.3. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>a convex lens of crystal,</b> used as a burning-glass, λίθος διαφανὴς ἀφ᾽ ἧς τὸ πῦρ ἅπτουσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 768, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Igne” 73. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>glass,</b> first in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 61b, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 389a8, and ὑαλῖτι; \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>glass-ware,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PFay. 134.4 (4th c.AD). \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> ὕαλος χνοώδης, in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.AD: Paulus Aegineta Medicus 6.22 \">Refs 7th c.AD+</a>], is <b>an absorbent</b> of some kind:—ὕαλος is also explained by βόρβορος in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus and 9th c.AD: Theognostus Grammaticus “Can.” 18\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]. [ῠᾰλος, as appears from [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 768 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—but late Poets make ῡ in some derivations to bring them into dactylic verses, ῡάλεος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 6.33, 12.249\">Refs</a>]; ῡέλινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 14.52\">Refs</a>]; ῡαλόεις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work]5.47\">Refs</a>]; ῡαλοειδής [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Lithica” 280 \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]; in iambic metre, ῡαλόχροα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 6.211.] \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G5194","accentedUnicode":"ὕαλος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5193","matchingForm":"ὑάλινος","stepTransliteration":"hualinos","gloss":"glass","_zh_tw_Gloss":"玻璃","_es_Gloss":"de vidrio","_zh_Gloss":"玻璃"}],"shortDef":"glass, some translate \"crystal\"","mediumDef":"glass, some translate \"crystal\" <br /><b>a transparent stone, crystal;</b>, also, <b>glass,</b> <ref='Rev.21.18, 21'>Rev. 21:18, 21</ref>*","stepGloss":"glass","stepTransliteration":"hualos","count":2,"_es_Definition":"vidrio, cristal","_zh_tw_Definition":"水晶","_zh_Definition":"水晶","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"thuỷ tinh (tinh thể). Xem G5205","_zh_tw_Gloss":"玻璃","_es_Gloss":"vidrio","_zh_Gloss":"玻璃"}]}